1.0beta2 - [RELEASEDATE]

- Added convenience method ezcConsoleOutput::outputLine(). This one adds a
  line break after outputting the desired text and works also without any
  text to print a blank line (similar to Pascals writeln()).
- Added option filter parameter to eczConsoleParameter::getHelp().
- Added a new class ezcConsoleOption to represent a single option (former
named parameter and used an array for the structure).
- Added new setting "mandatory" to ezcConsoleOption to indicate that an 
  option has to be submitted always.
- Added cell, row and table based format and alignment settings to
  ezcConsoleTable.
- Added real inheritence of format and alignment through ezcConsoleTable. 
- Added <borderFormat> property to rows to set a specific format for use when
  printing the row border.

- Refactored the whole package to fit into the unified layout and provide a
  much more convenient API.
- Changed to the use of structs, where it made sense, instead of complex array
  structures: ezcConsoleOptionRule, ezcConsoleOutputFormat, ezcConsoleOutputFormats, 
  ezcConsoleOutputOptions, ezcConsoleProgressbarOptions, eczConsoleTableOptions.
- Changed handling of parameter names in ezcConsoleInput, short and long parameters are now
  handled equally without their prefix everywhere.
- Changed to use overloading property access - __get(),__set(),__isset() -
  where possible (more convenient API).
- Changed handling of default values for ezcComponentOption.
- Changed handling ot table structure to classes ezcConsoleTableRow and ezcConsoleTableCell. 
  # These allow a new, innovative and very convenient way to create and customize console
  based tables: "$table[0][];" creates a new cell, "$table[2][]->format =
  'important';" creates a new cell and set's it's format to 'important',
  "$table[2]->align = ezcConsoleTable::ALIGN_CENTER;" set's the default
- Renamed ezcConsoleParameter to ezcConsoleInput (makes more sense, since
  Parameter sounded like an acronym for Option). Options are now handled
  through the ezcConsoleOption class.
- Renamed ezcConsoleOutput::styleText() to ezcConsoleOutput::formatText().
- Renamed ezcConsoleInput::fromString() to ezcConsoleInput::registerOptionString().

- Fixed bug with argument handling and non-value parameters in ezcConsoleInput.
- Fixed bug with submitting multiple parameters of the same name without value
in ezcConsoleInput.


1.0beta1 - [RELEASEDATE]

- Initial release of this package.
